        </p>

        <h4 class="font-semibold text-primary">2. Social Security & Health Levies (2024 / 2025 onwards)</h4>
        <p>
          Mandatory social security and insurance premiums are computed based on the selected country's rules:
          <ul class="list-disc pl-4 flex flex-col gap-1">
            <li><strong>United States</strong>: FICA Social Security (6.2% up to $168,600 cap) and Medicare (1.45% base, plus 0.9% additional surtax over $200k/$250k).</li>
            <li><strong>Canada</strong>: CPP pension contribution (5.95% up to $68,500 with $3,500 exemption) and EI premiums (1.66% up to $63,200).</li>
            <li><strong>United Kingdom</strong>: National Insurance Class 1 (8% between primary threshold and upper limit, 2% above).</li>
            <li><strong>Australia</strong>: Medicare Levy (2.0% flat of taxable income).</li>
            <li><strong>Germany</strong>: Social contributions bundle (Pension 9.3%, Health 7.3% + 1.7% supplement, Care 2.3%, Unemployment 1.3%) up to standard limits.</li>
            <li><strong>India</strong>: Health & Education Cess (4% of computed income tax).</li>
          </ul>
        </p>

        <h4 class="font-semibold text-primary">3. State, Provincial, or Local Taxes (2024 / 2025 onwards)</h4>
